The paper deals with transfer learning in deep neural networks for visual tasks, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of Representation Similarity Analysis (RSA) to assess the relationship between visual tasks and their task-specific models is a novel approach that falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper also evaluates the transfer learning performance on a new task, which involves semantic segmentation, a subfield of natural language processing (cs.CL).
